d, as a consequence,\n$\\mathscr{C}(\\mathcal{F})|\\mathscr{C}(\\mathcal{F})$ coincides with the constant\n1. Finally, by assuming $\\mathcal{F}$ p-consistent, we deepen some previous\ncharacterizations of p-entailment by showing that $\\mathcal{F}$ p-entails a\nconditional event $E_{n+1}|H_{n+1}$ if and only if the iterated conditional\n$(E_{n+1}|H_{n+1})\\,|\\,\\mathscr{C}(\\mathcal{F})$ is constant and equal to 1. We\nillustrate this characterization by an example related with weak transitivity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 10 Sep 2021 10:47:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 15 Sep 2021 16:09:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-16"}
